    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "body_blocks": [
                {
                  "inline": [
                    {
                      "kind": "text",
                      "text": "Drawn samples from the parameterized Laplace distribution."
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ],
              "data_type": "ndarray or scalar",
              "inline": [
                {
                  "kind": "text",
                  "text": "Drawn samples from the parameterized Laplace distribution."
                }
              ],
              "name": "out",
              "type": "field_list"
            }
          ],
          "title": "Returns",
          "type": "field_list"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Returns"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "It has the probability density function"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "formulas": [
            "f(x; \\mu, \\lambda) = \\frac{1}{2\\lambda} \\exp\\left(-\\frac{|x - \\mu|}{\\lambda}\\right)."
          ],
          "type": "math_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "The first law of Laplace, from 1774, states that the frequency\nof an error can be expressed as an exponential function of the\nabsolute magnitude of the error, which leads to the Laplace\ndistribution. For many problems in economics and health\nsciences, this distribution seems to model the data better\nthan the standard Gaussian distribution."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Notes"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "1\n\nAbramowitz, M. and Stegun, I. A. (Eds.). \"Handbook of\nMathematical Functions with Formulas, Graphs, and Mathematical\nTables, 9th printing,\" New York: Dover, 1972.",
          "type": "raw_block"
        },
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "2\n\nKotz, Samuel, et. al. \"The Laplace Distribution and\nGeneralizations, \" Birkhauser, 2001.",
          "type": "raw_block"
        },
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "3\n\nWeisstein, Eric W. \"Laplace Distribution.\"\nFrom MathWorld--A Wolfram Web Resource.\nhttps://mathworld.wolfram.com/LaplaceDistribution.html",
          "type": "raw_block"
        },
        {
          "raw_kind": "footnote",
          "raw_text": "4\n\nWikipedia, \"Laplace distribution\",\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Laplace_distribution",
          "type": "raw_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "References"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Draw samples from the distribution"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "loc, scale = 0., 1."
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "rng = flops.random.default_rng()"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "s = rng.laplace(loc, scale, 1000)"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Display the histogram of the samples, along with\nthe probability density function:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "count, bins, _ = plt.hist(s, 30, density=True)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "x = flops.arange(-8., 8., .01)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "pdf = flops.exp(-abs(x-loc)/scale)/(2.*scale)"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.plot(x, pdf)"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Plot Gaussian for comparison:"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "lines": [
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "g = (1/(scale * flops.sqrt(2 * flops.pi)) *"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": "...",
              "text": "flops.exp(-(x - loc)**2 / (2 * scale**2)))"
            },
            {
              "kind": "input",
              "prompt": ">>>",
              "text": "plt.plot(x,g)"
            }
          ],
          "type": "doctest_block"
        }
      ],
      "title": "Examples"
    }
  ],
